## 3. Knowledge Base Design

| Knowledge source | What it contains | Freshness required | Owner |
|---|---|---|---|
| Provider directory | In-network specialists by type, location, accepting new patients status | Weekly sync | Engineering |
| Insurance eligibility API | Patient coverage, specialist visit copay, deductible status | Real-time | Engineering |
| Prior authorization rules | Procedure codes requiring auth by insurance plan | Daily sync | Engineering |
| Specialist availability API | Open appointment slots by provider and location | Real-time | Engineering |
| Patient profile | Insurance ID, location, language preference, contact channel | Session initialization | Engineering |
| Referral record | Referring provider, specialty type, urgency flag, ICD codes | Session initialization | Engineering |

---

## 4. Memory Design

| Memory type | What to store | When to store | When to clear |
|---|---|---|---|
| Session memory | Referral details, eligibility result, specialists presented, patient selection | After each step | End of session |
| Cross-session memory | Prior specialist visits, stated location preferences, communication preferences | Session initialization | Per HIPAA retention policy |
| Pre-session context | Active referrals, pending authorizations, open appointments | Session initialization | End of session |

**MUST:** Verify insurance eligibility before presenting specialist options — never book an appointment that may not be covered

**MUST NOT:** Share referral diagnosis codes or clinical notes with patient-facing responses — clinical detail stays within provider systems

