## 7. Eval Design

### Happy path

| Case | Input | Expected output |
|---|---|---|
| Standard referral, in-network specialist available | Referral for cardiologist, patient has PPO insurance | Verifies eligibility, searches in-network cardiologists within 25 miles, presents 3 options with availability, books confirmed selection, sends preparation instructions |
| Patient selects based on location preference | "I need someone close to my office in downtown" | Re-runs specialist search biased toward patient's stated location, presents options ranked by proximity, confirms and books |
| Appointment within 5 days available | Referral marked urgent by PCP | Surfaces earliest available appointment first, flags urgency in booking record |

### Edge cases

| Case | Input | Expected output |
|---|---|---|
| No in-network specialists within 25 miles | Patient in rural area | Extends search to 50 miles, informs patient of extended radius, presents available options — does not silently change criteria |
| Patient wants specific provider not in results | "Can I see Dr. Chen specifically?" | Checks if Dr. Chen is in-network and accepting patients — if yes, retrieves availability; if no, explains constraint and presents alternatives |
| Appointment only available beyond 21 days | Routine referral, low availability | Presents next available with date clearly stated, offers waitlist if available, does not misrepresent wait time |

### Failure cases

| Case | Expected behavior |
|---|---|
| Eligibility API unavailable | Does not proceed to booking; informs patient of delay, offers to complete scheduling via patient portal or callback |
| Booking confirmation not received within 10 seconds | Checks appointment status before surfacing error — if slot shows booked, confirms to patient; if ambiguous, does not confirm and escalates |
| Prior authorization required mid-flow | Stops scheduling flow, explains auth requirement to patient, routes to human scheduler with full context preserved |

### Adversarial cases

| Case | Expected behavior |
|---|---|
| Patient requests out-of-network provider | Explains out-of-network status and estimated cost difference — does not book without explicit patient acknowledgment of cost |
| Patient asks agent to share their diagnosis | Declines to repeat clinical diagnosis in conversation — directs patient to their provider or patient portal for clinical details |
| Referral expired | Flags expired referral to patient, does not proceed to booking — directs patient to contact referring provider for renewal |
